How you boys making out?

819
01:04:37,240 --> 01:04:38,537
Just about finished!

820
01:04:38,741 --> 01:04:40,368
Hurry up, will you?

821
01:04:40,576 --> 01:04:42,203
Better get out of here
before those krauts get here.

822
01:04:42,411 --> 01:04:43,673
You need any help?

823
01:04:43,846 --> 01:04:45,438
I got a good idea.

824
01:04:45,648 --> 01:04:47,275
We'll give them all a hot water bottle.

825
01:04:47,483 --> 01:04:51,214
That water comes off the ice.

826
01:04:51,420 --> 01:04:54,116
I'm loaded with C-4 need any?

827
01:04:54,323 --> 01:04:58,191
They could sell you some.

828
01:04:58,394 --> 01:05:01,295
Drive on.

829
01:05:06,402 --> 01:05:11,863
Why you got your wires
hooked onto that detonator?

830
01:05:12,742 --> 01:05:14,437
I guess he's in a hurry.

831
01:05:14,644 --> 01:05:17,306
To get killed? That's not the way.

832
01:05:17,513 --> 01:05:19,037
Sarge, bring a couple of men.

833
01:05:19,248 --> 01:05:25,209
We'll look under that bridge.

834
01:05:37,199 --> 01:05:38,097
This ain't the road to Ambleve.

835
01:05:38,301 --> 01:05:39,393
This is taking us to malmedy.

836
01:05:39,602 --> 01:05:42,162
The sign says that-away.

837
01:05:42,371 --> 01:05:44,339
The map says Ambleve was this way.

838
01:05:44,540 --> 01:05:49,534
Somebody straighten this out.

839
01:05:49,745 --> 01:05:53,704
Ambleve. Ambleve...

840
01:05:56,085 --> 01:05:57,211
Hey, Wolenskl!

841
01:05:57,420 --> 01:06:00,150
Oh, Colonel.

842
01:06:00,356 --> 01:06:01,914
We're all fouled up here.

843
01:06:02,124 --> 01:06:03,182
We've been ordered to Ambleve,

844
01:06:03,392 --> 01:06:04,256
But the maps are wrong.

845
01:06:04,460 --> 01:06:07,793
They don't jibe with the signs.

846
01:06:07,997 --> 01:06:08,986
This will take you to malmedy.

847
01:06:09,198 --> 01:06:11,632
Ambleve's that way.

848
01:06:11,834 --> 01:06:14,496
We've been following these
signs the whole way.

849
01:06:14,704 --> 01:06:20,472
The MPs we ran into directed
us this way.

850
01:06:20,676 --> 01:06:23,270
They've been changed.
They switched them around.

851
01:06:23,479 --> 01:06:25,845
Those MPs seem ok to you?

852
01:06:26,048 --> 01:06:26,776
What do you mean?

853
01:06:26,949 --> 01:06:29,076
Anything odd about them?

854
01:06:29,285 --> 01:06:30,582
Just regular Cls.

855
01:06:30,786 --> 01:06:32,777
We intercepted an enemy
dispatch a few days ago

856
01:06:32,955 --> 01:06:35,355
Recruiting english-speaking Germans.

857
01:06:35,558 --> 01:06:38,356
When did you cross the river?

858
01:06:38,561 --> 01:06:40,290
8:40. We were the last ones across.

859
01:06:40,496 --> 01:06:41,895
They were going to blow it.

860
01:06:42,098 --> 01:06:43,258
Did you see the bridge blow?

861
01:06:43,466 --> 01:06:46,799
No, but engineers were setting charges.

862
01:06:46,969 --> 01:06:50,234
Hey, wait a minute. What the hell?

863
01:06:50,439 --> 01:06:54,967
They weren't engineers. They were MPs!

864
01:06:55,177 --> 01:06:57,407
Murphy, get me headquarters!

865
01:06:57,613 --> 01:07:00,582
Major, have someone switch
that sign back!

866
01:07:00,783 --> 01:07:01,841
Red river 6, red river 6...

867
01:07:02,051 --> 01:07:03,450
Come in, red river 6.

868
01:07:03,652 --> 01:07:05,279
Come in, red river 2.

869
01:07:05,488 --> 01:07:07,786
Red river 6, this is red river 2.

870
01:07:07,990 --> 01:07:10,151
Germans uniformed as american MPs

871
01:07:10,359 --> 01:07:12,657
Holding our river bridge.

872
01:07:12,862 --> 01:07:15,353
Bridge has not been blown.

873
01:07:15,564 --> 01:07:18,897
Repeat.
Germans uniformed as american Mps

874
01:07:19,101 --> 01:07:21,160
Holding our river bridge.

875
01:07:21,370 --> 01:07:23,270
Bridge has not been blown.

876
01:07:23,472 --> 01:07:24,666
Over and out.

877
01:07:24,874 --> 01:07:27,843
Let's go!

878
01:07:42,191 --> 01:07:46,150
Better hold it, Jack.

879
01:07:47,263 --> 01:07:48,093
What happened?

880
01:07:48,297 --> 01:07:51,960
They ran into a fire fight,
German patrol.

881
01:07:52,168 --> 01:07:54,193
I don't see any Germans.

882
01:07:54,403 --> 01:07:55,427
They're in the river.

883
01:07:55,638 --> 01:07:57,162
They didn't make it across.

884
01:07:57,373 --> 01:07:59,898
Get out of here.
We're blowing the bridge.

885
01:08:00,109 --> 01:08:01,599
What?

886
01:08:01,811 --> 01:08:03,369
Are you sure?

887
01:08:03,579 --> 01:08:09,540
Watch out. The MPs are krauts!

888
01:08:31,907 --> 01:08:35,866
Oh, my god! Get down!

889
01:09:04,840 --> 01:09:08,276
Why are we waiting?
Get that tank out of the way.

890
01:09:08,511 --> 01:09:11,742
We're preparing to tow it, sir.

891
01:09:11,947 --> 01:09:13,346
Tiger to tanks leopard and panther.

892
01:09:13,549 --> 01:09:19,510
Blast that tanks off the bridge.

893
01:09:32,501 --> 01:09:33,991
It's headquarters, Colonel.

894
01:09:34,203 --> 01:09:36,831
General Kohler says
we are behind schedule.

895
01:09:37,039 --> 01:09:39,735
He wants to know what's holding us up.

896
01:09:39,942 --> 01:09:45,437
Tell the General the Americans are
learning how to retreat.

897
01:09:45,648 --> 01:09:53,111
Tiger to panther. Get onto the bridge
push that junk right out of.

898
01:10:28,190 --> 01:10:32,183
The way. Stay down.

899
01:10:43,005 --> 01:10:47,339
Phy, call headquarters tell them the
our river bridge

900
01:10:47,543 --> 01:10:49,010
The enemy's crossing
in great strength.

901
01:10:49,211 --> 01:10:52,203
Yes, sir.

902
01:11:02,191 --> 01:11:03,556
Let me have your rifle.

903
01:11:03,759 --> 01:11:05,351
What you need is a cannon, sir.

904
01:11:05,561 --> 01:11:06,220
Last time I saw him

905
01:11:06,462 --> 01:11:11,422
All I had was a camera.

906
01:11:53,075 --> 01:11:54,235
Can't you hurry it up, Sergeant?

907
01:11:54,443 --> 01:11:55,808
We lost the column.

908
01:11:56,011 --> 01:11:57,911
You happen to have a new carburetor in
your pocket

909
01:11:58,113 --> 01:12:00,877
Lieutenant?

910
01:12:01,083 --> 01:12:05,577
You mean we're stuck here?

911
01:12:05,788 --> 01:12:10,748
Nope. We can still walk.

912
01:12:11,794 --> 01:12:14,763
Let's go.

913
01:12:15,631 --> 01:12:17,690
Hey, maybe we can get a lift, huh?

914
01:12:17,900 --> 01:12:20,869
Hold it.

915
01:12:22,805 --> 01:12:28,266
We better find out
just who they are first.

916
01:12:31,213 --> 01:12:34,182
Down.

917
01:12:38,721 --> 01:12:42,680
Yeah, Krauts. Back.


